More world leaders have congratulated president Muhammadu Buhari on his re-election. Among them  was King Salman bin Abdulaziz Al Saud of Saudi Arabia who phoned president Buhari. In a telephone conversation with the president, the Saudi King, who is the Custodian of the Two Holy Mosques, wished Buhari success and good health in his second term in office. President Buhari expressed appreciation to the King. Also, the Emir of Qatar Sheikh Tamim bin Hamad Al Thani sent a cable of congratulations to President Buhari on his re-election, wishing the Nigerian President success and the Nigerian people further development and progress. Russian Ambassador to Nigeria, Alexey Shebarshin, also sent a congratulatory message. UK Minister of State for Africa, Harriett Baldwin, said: “I offer my congratulations to President Buhari on securing a second term as the Nigerian President. French Ministry for Europe and Foreign Affairs also congratulated the president. President Buhari has also received congratulatory messages from Presidents Emmerson Mnangagwa of Zimbabwe, Cyril Ramaphosa of South Africa and Uhuru Kenyatta of Kenya. African leaders congratulate Buhari on re-election Buhari congratulates Chinese president on re-election Buhari congratulates Chinese president on re-election